19/04/2006
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- British Minister of State for the Armed Forces Adam Ingram visited Kosovo on Tuesday (18 April). It was the first stop on a regional tour meant to demonstrate the importance Britain attaches to the stability and prosperity of the Balkans. In Pristina, Ingram reaffirmed support for the development of the Kosovo Protection Corps and discussed the progress of several related UN-backed projects. On Wednesday he is visiting Bosnia and Herzegovina, with stops in Sarajevo and Banja Luka. (Government News Network, KosovaLive, Fena - 18/04/06)
